AKURE – Residents of Akoko communities and a socio-political group, Elevate Nigeria, on Sunday commended member of House of Representatives, Representing Akoko North East/North West Federal Constituency, Mr. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo, for facilitating and delivering 12 brand new 500KVA transformers to the constituency. A statement signed by the group’s Coordinator, Mr. Tola Davis, and made available to newsmen in Akure, the state capital on Sunday, described the move Hon. Tunji-Ojo as means of engendering economic development and growth in all the communities in the constituency. According to the statement, “The unprecedented achievements of Hon. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo in the federal Constituency is one which has continued to give the people of the region great joy and satisfaction that they have indeed made the right choice. “His representation is one which has also made people from various regions wishing that they have a representative like Hon. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo. “The transformer which have been delivered already is expected to be installed in twelve communities in order to resolve the challenge of inadequate power supply in the region. “This no doubt will serve as a major boost to the industrialization effort of the federal lawmaker in the Federal Constituency, it would also be recalled that Hon. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo has started and completed the renovation and rehabilitation of many road network in the region all as part of his move to open up the region for more economic development.”